-- Polish Stocks: Kernel, PKN Orlen Shares Are Active in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 2012-06-25T16:06:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/polish-stocks-pkn-orlen-kernel-shares-are-active-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  lost 1.5
percent to 2,208.35 in Warsaw, its fourth day of losses.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Kernel Holding SA (KER PW), Ukraine’s biggest sunflower-oil
producer, dropped 1.5 percent to 59.5 zloty. A unit received a
revolving credit of $210 million from a group of European banks,
the company said in a regulatory statement today.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN)  , Poland’s largest oil refiner,
retreated 1.1 percent to a one-week low of 35.8 zloty. Oil
traded below $80 a barrel for a third day in New York after a
report indicated that central banks will struggle to boost
global economic growth.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
 pskolimowski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
